The paper deals with hyperparameter optimization, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of reinforcement learning to address this problem suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of surrogate models and acquisition functions, which are commonly used in optimization problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve a large battery of datasets, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning to optimize hyperparameters can be seen as a control problem, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
